import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['fertility'])
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='fertility', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    median_fertility = data['fertility'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_fertility, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_fertility:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility across all countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expect', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('How has life expectancy changed over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Life Expectancy', loc='upper left')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='country', y='fertility', data=data, color='blue', label='Actual Fertility Rate')
    sns.barplot(x='country', y='p_fertility', data=data, color='green', label='Predicted Fertility Rate')
    
    plt.title('How do the fertility rates of different countries compare to their predicted fertility rates?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
